rComments: I took a first year seminar of him. Governing the New Europe. It was really hard to not to fall asleep during class, he  has really monotone tone. Besides on our essays, he expected us to write like his 3rd or 4th years courses which is quite challenging for a first year student.

The most informative class I've ever taken. A very kind man who is a walking, talking encyclopedia! It's a shame that there aren't more teachers like him at this school. Do not be intimidated, he's an incredible prof with a great sense of humour! :P
